swap.t.sol
├── when call is reentrant
│  └── it should revert
└── when call is not reentrant
   ├── when the module is suspended
   │  └── it should revert with Suspended
   └── when the module is not suspended
      ├── when the module is paused
      │  └── it should revert with Paused
      └── when the module is not paused
         ├── when caller is not a registered operator
         │  └── it should revert with UnauthorizedCaller
         └── when caller is a registered operator
            ├── given lockdown mode is off
            │  ├── given the swap order fails to be executed
            │  │  └── it should revert
            │  └── given the swap order is successfuly executed
            │     ├── given the output amount is smaller that given minimum
            │     │  └── it should revert with AmountOutTooLow
            │     └── given the output amount is not smaller that given minimum
            │        ├── order.inputAmount of order.inputToken should have been spent in the module's safe
            │        ├── fees, if any, should have been received by fee collector
            │        └── at least order.minOutputAmount of order.outputToken, minus eventual fees, should have been received by the module's safe
            └── given lockdown mode is on
               ├── when the swap order has an input or output token for which price data is not registered
               │  └── it should revert with PriceFeedRouteNotRegistered
               └── when the swap order have input and output tokens with registered price data
                  ├── given the swap order fails to be executed
                  │  └── it should revert
                  └── given the swap order is successfuly executed
                     ├── given the output amount is smaller that given minimum
                     │  └── it should revert with AmountOutTooLow
                     └── given the output amount is not smaller that given minimum
                        ├── given the value loss induced by one of the swaps is higher than maxSwapLossBps
                        │  └── it should revert with MaxValueLossExceeded
                        └── given no value loss induced by any of the swaps is higher than maxSwapLossBps
                           ├── order.inputAmount of order.inputToken should have been spent in the module's safe
                           ├── fees, if any, should have been received by fee collector
                           └── at least order.minOutputAmount of order.outputToken, minus eventual fees, should have been received by the module's safe
